#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:37
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:30
msgid "How to use sample template"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:39
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:32
msgid ""
"Replace sample content with your own content. For example, replace -Add "
"description of appointment- with your content."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:40
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:33
msgid "Give full name and acronym at first mention of your agency or department."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:41
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:34
msgid ""
"Delete any sample content that you do not need. <b>We recommend keeping "
"messages short and to the point.</b>"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:42
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:35
msgid ""
"If adding more content, use simple words, inclusive language and short "
"sentences. For more on plain language, visit canada.ca's <a "
"href='https://design.canada.ca/style-guide/'>content style guide</a>"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:46
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:39
msgid "Quick tips for English messages"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:48
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:41
msgid "Avoid words like 'please' and 'sorry'."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:49
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:42
msgid ""
"Use active voice. For example 'We may dismiss your application' instead "
"of 'Your application will be dismissed'."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:50
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:43
msgid ""
"Use commands to give instructions, for example 'Reschedule' instead of "
"'You should reschedule'."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:51
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:44
msgid "Use positive contractions like 'We're meeting'."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:52
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:45
msgid "Spell out negative contractions like 'We cannot meet'."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:56
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:49
msgid "Quick tips for French messages"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:58
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:51
msgid ""
"Write short and clear texts by starting with the most important "
"information and avoiding unnecessary content that could distract the "
"reader. Instead of 'Lors de votre arrivée sur les lieux, merci de bien "
"vouloir fournir une preuve d'identité, qu'il s'agisse d'un passeport ou "
"d'un autre document délivré par le gouvernement fédéral', use 'À votre "
"arrivée, présentez un document d'identité fédéral.'"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:59
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:52
msgid ""
"Use simple words and avoid jargon. For example, instead of 'Le dossier "
"sera traité conformément au principe de caducité' use 'Le dossier sera "
"fermé, car il n'est plus valide'."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:60
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:53
msgid ""
"Use gender neutral wording as much as possible. You can use words that "
"have one form to indicate either sex, like individu ('individual') or "
"personne ('person') to replace femme ('woman') or homme ('man'). For "
"groups of people, use neutral collective terms to avoid specifying the "
"gender (for instance, use the term personnel ['the staff'] rather than "
"the gendered plural les employés or employées ['the employees'].)"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:61
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:54
msgid ""
"Use the active or passive voice based on the context. Active or passive "
"voice may be options to avoid gendered sentences. Use the voice that "
"reads most naturally in French."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:62
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:55
msgid ""
"Use the positive form as much as possible and reserve the negative for "
"when consequences could be grave or fatal. Avoid double negations and "
"exceptions to exceptions, which could confuse readers."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:76
#: app/templates/views/edit-sms-template.html:81
msgid ""
"This will not show in the message. Use a name that helps you find the "
"template when you need it."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/edit-email-template.html:77
msgid "Tell recipients what the email is about. Try to use less than 10 words."
msgstr ""

