"Every time you sign in you will be asked for a second type of "
"verification."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:23
msgid "Not sure which method to choose? Learn more about 2FA"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:26
msgid ""
"Two-step verification adds an extra layer of security to your account by "
"requiring something in addition to your password when you sign in to "
"Notify."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:28
msgid ""
"Here’s a simple overview of the two-step verification methods available "
"on Notify:"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:31
msgid "Security Key (best option)"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:33
msgid "Security keys are physical devices, like YubiKey."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:34
msgid ""
"They offer the highest level of security since you need to have the key "
"on you for authentication, making it harder for phishing attacks to "
"succeed."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:39
msgid ""
"You can use your email for two-step verification, but it’s not the "
"quickest or safest option."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:40
msgid ""
"It depends on your access to your email and can be at risk from phishing "
"and other attacks."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:43
msgid "SMS Text Message (least secure option)"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:45
msgid ""
"This method sends a code to your phone through a text message, making it "
"faster than email."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/views/user-profile/2fa.html:46
msgid ""
"However, it’s considered less secure than other methods due to risks like"
" SIM swapping and other types of attacks."
msgstr ""

